<p>
<seg id=1> Prime Minister of Israel Ehud Barak appointed Shimon Peres, the most hardliner of the Israel government, Foreign Minister of Israel. </seg>
<seg id=2> The appointment was made just before the American Summit Conference on an interim agreement of peace between the leaders of Israel and Palestine. </seg>
<seg id=3> According to the agreement, Israel would hand over more areas of the West Bank to Palestine. </seg>
<seg id=4> Shimon was determined to build more Jewish settlements and fight against any compromise on withdrawing the army. </seg>
</p>
